column12: Device and method for securing an article against theft
column13: Die Erfindung betrifft eine Vorrichtung und ein Verfahren zur elektronischen Artikelüberwachung, bestehend aus einem Sicherungselement (3), das mit einem zu sichernden Artikel (1) verbunden ist und durch ein innerhalb einer Abfragezone erzeugtes magnetisches Wechselfeld zur Aussendung eines charakteristischen Signals angeregt wird, wodurch ein Alarm ausgelöst wird. Der Erfindung liegt die Aufgabe zugrunde, eine Vorrichtung bzw. ein Verfahren vorzuschlagen, die bzw. das das Entfernen eines Sicherungselementes (3) von einem gesicherten Artikel (1) erheblich erschwert. Hinsichtlich der Vorrichtung wird die Aufgabe dadurch gelöst, daß eine Schutzfolie (2) vorgesehen ist, die das Sicherungselement (3) vollständig und den Artikel (1) zumindest im Bereich des Sicherungselementes (3) abdeckt.

column12: Sausage unloading machine into curing carts
column13: Machine for unloading sausages from curing trolleys. The machine is designed to unload the rods loaded with sausages that are stacked at different levels on moveable trolleys situated in curing chambers. Said machine is based on a fixed structure (1) into which is moved the corresponding trolley (16) carrying the rods loaded with sausages, the structure (1) has a trolley bridge (4) which can move up and down and has side and upper arms (5) and conveyor belts (6) on which the sausage carrying bars are placed in order to carry them towards the exit zone where there are guiding beams (14) complemented with rolling guard rods (14) with an external fixed support belonging to the fixed structure (1). The arms (5) of the trolley-bridge (4) move under the different sausage-carrying rods and a slight upward movement of the trolley (4) will move the rods on to the conveyor belt (6) and carry them towards the exit zone.<IMAGE>

column12: A DEVICE AND A METHOD FOR SAFEGUARDING AN ARTICLE AGAINST THEFT
column13: The invention relates to a device and a method for electronic supervision of articles, consisting of a security element which is connected to an article to be safeguarded and which is excited by a magnetic alternating field generated within an inquiry zone to send a characteristic signal by which an alarm is triggered. The objective of the invention is to propose a device and a method which respectively render removal of a security element from an article to be safeguarded considerably difficult. The task is solved by the device in that a protective film is provided which completely covers the security element and the article at least in the area of the security element.
column15: AGUILAR PEDRO LLORT

column12: Vorrichtung und Verfahren zur Sicherung eines Artikels gegen Diebstahl
column13: The device includes a strip of easily magnetised material (3.1) inserted between an article (1) and its film covering, which is a laminate in which the strip can be embedded. Alternative embodiments are a thin-film security tag and one incorporating a resonant oscillatory circuit. When an attempt is made to carry the article through an alternating magnetic field in a monitoring zone, a characteristic signal is emitted and an alarm is triggered. The resonant-circuit variant may comprise two capacitor plates separated by a dielectric layer and interconnected by a spiral flat conductor.

column12: IDENTIFYING BACKGROUND AUDIO IN BROADCAST SIGNALS USING MULTIPLE SOURCES
column13: Methods and devices for identifying background audio signals in broadcast audio signals using multiple sources are disclosed. First audio files with the isolated background audio signals are received from a first source, such as a mixer through, e.g., a communication channel and second audio files with the broadcast audio signals are received from a second source through, e.g., a broadcast transmission channel. Then, presence of the background audio signals is identified in the broadcast audio signals.

column12: METHOD FOR PREPARING ACTIVATED CARBON AT LOW TEMPERATURE FROM BIOSOLIDS.
column13: The present disclosure is related to a method for preparing activated carbon at low temperature from biosolids, generated in wastewater treatment plants. The method is characterized in that activated carbon is obtained by a thermal treatment of wet biosolids at low temperature and a short processing time. This excludes the stages of preliminary water dehydration present in the biosolids, drying, high carbonization temperatures in furnaces at 800-1000°C, and subsequent activation of the remaining carbon.

column12: METHOD FOR PRODUCING POROUS CARBONIZED CERAMICS.
column13: The present invention relates to porous carbonized ceramics, which contributes to avoid the environmental contamination of large-scale industrial wastes. The processing of such wastes in a single technological process, allows obtaining innovative materials with novel properties. Said technologies includes the production of filter construction ceramics, involving energy and water savings, which provides a low cost of products. Said formulations are based on red clay, crushed glass, and tezontle residues, allowing obtaining said ceramics at low temperatures and short cooking times. Also, the introduction of bio solids containing up 50% to 60% water in the mixtures allows the molding of plastics without using water in the process cycle, thus implementing water-saving technology. Further, the ceramic products (bricks, tiles) are of different porosities and different carbon content, depending on the resistance used in various engineering areas.

column12: METHOD FOR THE ELABORATION OF BRICKS FROM BIOSOLIDS, SAVING WATER AND ENERGY.
column13: The present invention describes the development of energy-saving technologies, which bases on the eutectic formation principle of low-temperature and the mixing mechanism of liquid-solid-phase sintering when a low melting point component work as a ligament for the refractory components - aluminosilicates. The time and temperature of sintering reduce by the development of various compositions of the red clay such as 1) waste glass crushed with biosolids, 2) crushed waste of tezontle and biosolids, and 3) crushed waste of glass and tezontle plus biosolids. All of that results in the obtainment of bricks with excellent mechanical properties at low sintering temperatures of up 800°C to 100°C (as compared to a standard temperature of up 1050°C to 1100°C) and with a reduced cooking time from 8 to 24 hours. Modifying the content of glass and tezontle in mixtures, the open porosity of the products is varied, and the amount of water absorption changes from W=25% to W<1%.

column12: ELABORATION OF GYPSUM PLASTERBOARDS WITH RECYCLED MATERIALS AND FIBERS.
column13: The present invention relates to a method for the preparation of gypsum plasterboards with a secondary hemi-hydrated calcium sulfate, calcium sulfate, glass powder and different fibers (loofah or coconut shell or glass) or polymer mesh thereby coated by both Sides with layers of multi-leaf cellulose. Secondary hydrated calcium sulfate has the composition CaSO4 · 2H2O, which is recycled at different temperatures to obtain secondary hemihydrate calcium sulfate and calcium sulfate. Glass is obtained by grinding glass bottles and passed through a sieving process to obtain the required particle size. The mixture comprising the secondary calcium sulfate, calcium sulfate, glass powder and fibers (coconut shell or loofah or glass or polymer mesh) is hydrated and compacted into a laminated gypsum plasterboard which is coated by layers of cellulose for their use as panels. Excellent results are obtained when we add the fibers as compared to the samples that do not contain them.
column14: UNIV AUTONOMA DEL ESTADO DE MORELOS

column12: A SURFACE-COATING MIXTURE.
column13: The present invention relates to a method for preparing a surface-coating mixture made from recycled materials, including secondary hemihydrate calcium sulfate, calcium sulfate and preferably transparent glass containers, which are a waste from industry and society. Because the secondary hydrated calcium sulfate includes a CaSO4 2H2O composition, it is subjected to a recycling process through dehydration by thermal treatment. In the case of glass, it is only a question of reducing the containers to be recycled by a grinding treatment, shifting them to obtain different particle sizes. With the mixture of calcium sulfate hemihydrate, calcium sulfate, and glass powders, an YV mixture is obtained which is hydrated for use as a coating. It is shown that the favorable conditions for the material with greater strength and durability, are the sulfate powders of calcium, glass, and water.

column12: MIXTURE FOR MANUFACTURING BRICKS.
column13: The present invention refers to a mixture for manufacturing ceramic bricks, with the advantage of reducing the sintering time and temperature of products made of red clay bricks. Different compositions were developed: 1) red clay-crushed residues of fusible glass (broken glass (or containers of broken glass)); 2) red clay-crushed residues of tezontle stone, 3) red clay-residues of crushed fusible glass and tezontle stone. The performed studies shown that using the standard techniques of cooking brick products, based on the obtained mixtures, will result in bricks of suitable mechanical properties at low sintering temperatures ranging from 800°C to 1000°C (compared to a standard temperature ranging from 1050°C to 1100°C) and with a substantially reduced sintering time ranging from 8 h to 24 h (compared to the standard period of time of 72 h).

column12: Multilevel-clamped multilevel converters (MLC2)
column13: The present invention discloses the  multilevel-clamped multilevel converter  (MLC 2 ) . In this invention the multilevel clamping concept is devised, whereby a DC bus voltage, comprised of multiple DC bus voltage nodes, is managed by one or more  multilevel clamping units  (MCUs)  to convey a higher number of levels for synthesizing the output waveforms of a DC-AC multipoint clamped  (MPC)  power conversion structure. Thus the resultant converter has the number of levels increased when compared with conventional  MPC  multilevel solutions, which is very important for improving power quality, while the overall structure is kept simple, wherein the number of components can be considerably reduced.

column12: SISTEMA DE PREVENCION CONTRA LA INFESTACION DE PIOJOS.
column13: Sistema de prevención contra la infestación de piojos. Mediante este sistema se previene al usuario que utilice el dispositivo en el que se materializa aquél contra la infestación de piojos, constituyendo además un medio eficaz para combatir infestaciones ya existentes.

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO MEJORADO PARA PREPARAR UNA COMPOSICION CATALITICA PARA LA DESHIDROGENACION DE HIDROCARBUROS Y PRODUCTO RESULTANTE
column13: La presente invención se refiere a un procedimiento mejorado para preparar una composición catalítica para la deshidrogenación de hidrocarburos, caracterizado porque comprende las siguientes etapas: preparar un soporte catalítico, a partir de una mezcla de nitratos de aluminio y zinc, agregar a la mezcla agua desmineralizada y posteriormente añadirla simultáneamente junto con una solución de hidróxido de amonio, a un sistema que contiene agua desmineralizada en un rango de temperaturas de 25 a 75 grados C, filtrar y lavar el gel contenido con agua desmineralizada, secar a vacío el sólido alrededor de 24 horas a temperaturas cercanas a 120 grados C, calcinar en dos etapas el mismo sólido llevándose a cabo la primera etapa en un rango de temperaturas de 400 a 600 grados C de 4 a 6 horas; impregnar al soporte catalítico con una solución acuosa de cloruro estañoso; secar a vacío el sólido catalítico con una solución de ácido cloroplatínico; secar a vacío el catalizador formado, en un rango de temperaturas entre 80 a 120 grados C durante 2 a 10 horas; calcinar bajo una corriente de aire seco de 30 a 500 grados C de temperatura durante 2 a 4 horas.

column12: PVC/GRAPHENE OXIDE MEMBRANE WITH ADDITIVES AND FILLERS FOR THE REMOVAL OF CONTAMINANTS IN WATER AND PROCESS TO MANUFACTURE IT.
column13: The present invention relates to some filtration membranes and their process for manufacturing membranes for water filtration from polyvinyl chloride (PVC), graphene oxide (GO), process additives, and fillers used in the water industry. Also, it possesses the advantage of using a low-cost polymer, polyvinyl chloride (PVC), and conventional additives in PVC technology. Said device is beneficial for clarification of beverages, purification of antibiotics, removal of bacteria, retention of alcohol in drinks, drying of solvents, desalination of seawater, removal of heavy metals, retention of particles suspended in air, retention of different fractions in physiological fluids, purification of raw water, and purification of wastewater.

column12: PROCESS FOR THE SEMI-PREPARATIVE SCALE PURIFICATION AND RECOVERY OF ELLAGITANNINS AND PUNICALAGIN.
column13: The present invention relates to a method for the separation, purification and recovery of ellagitannins, punicalagin and soluble compounds in organic solvents, from polyphenols of pomegranate shell using Medium Pressure Liquid Chromatography (MPLC). The said method consists of a certain number of conditions, using as a stationary phase a semi-preparative reverse phase column C -18. Then, as a mobile phase the design of methanol and water combination, thus allowing the elution of the polar compounds, and acetonitrile and water combination, thereby washing said column and obtaining the compounds soluble in organic solvents. Subsequently, the solvent evaporates in the fractions, re-suspended in water and freeze-dried, and characterizes by HPLC on an analytical scale and by ESI-MS.

column12: ELECTRONIC MONITOR FOR HEALTH THROUGH CLOTHING ITEMS.
column13: The present disclosure is related to a wearable electronic device for monitoring clinical variables of one or more users under observation through body wireless technology as a bridge to communicate clinical variables of a person directly from his body to a database which stores temperature behavior, fall detection, electrocardiogram and geographical location in a controlled or uncontrolled environment; which may be accessed through a mobile or web interface directly in the controlled environment or on the Internet. This invention includes a modified t-shirt on both the front and rear sides thereof with an elastic band which is innerly woven into the t-shirt so as to surround the top of the rib cage and clinical sensors of a conductive fabric which have communication lines woven into the elastic band and the t-shirt, allowing communication with a controller device. Said controller comprises a processing module referred to as "SoC", a navigation module, an input and output module refe rred to as "I/O", a wireless communication module, a nonvolatile storage module referred to as "memory" and a set of communication channels between the synchronous/asynchronous modules. This invention also includes a method to detect a critical fall and not a false alarm, such as an abrupt movement, a jump etc.

column12: DC time-multiplexed power converter and its modulation technique
column13: This invention deals with a power processing system able to process the  power exchanged between an alternating current (AC) network {7} and multiple direct current (DC) elements {1} by time-multiplexing their connection {3} to the DC side of a DC/AC full-bridge (FB) power converter { 4 }.  This is the reason why this invention has been named  DC Time-Multiplexed Power Processor  and its acronym is  DCM- xyz , where  x  is the number of DC ports {2} of the power processing structure,  y  is the number AC phases, and  z  is the number of voltage levels used in the DC/AC power conversion process. Even though the DCM- xyz  power processing structure was technically designed to work as an inverter in grid-connected PV power generation systems, i.e., delivering the power generated by the multiple DC PV panels to an AC grid, it can also operate as a rectifier if necessary, i.e., supplying multiple DC loads from the power consumed from the AC grid. Moreover, when the DCM- xyz  power processing structure operates in inverter mode, its DC ports can be supplied by any primary energy source other than the PV one. The DC system of the DCM- xyz  power processing structure can be constituted by a number higher than one of DC ports ( x ), and any arbitrary number of AC phases ( y ), being feasible to use any arbitrary number of voltage levels ( z ) in its power converter.

column12: DNA MOLECULE CODING FOR A GAMMA-TOCOPHEROL METHYLTRANSFERASE IN MAIZE AND APPLICATIONS THEREOF
column13: The invention relates to a DNA molecule comprising: (a) a DNA sequence which is identified by SEQ ID No. 1, or (b) a DNA sequence similar to the latter, which (i) is essentially homologous to same and/or which (ii) codes for a polypeptide which is essentially homologous to the protein encoded by the above-mentioned DNA molecule. When introduced into a tocopherol-producing plant, principally maize, using standard biotechnology techniques, the aforementioned DNA molecule enables an increase in the total vitamin E content of said plant as wells in the concentrations of α and ?-tocopherol. The invention can also be used for other applications.

column12: aparelhos de conformação, peça tubular, processo de conformação por clinching contínuo com cavidade central e usos
column13: a presente tecnologia refere-se a aparelhos de conformação para a produção de uma peça tubular com uma ou mais cavidades centrais tubulares, em única etapa de fabricação, a partir de um processo de conformação mecânica por clinching contínuo com cavidade central. os aparelhos de conformação consistem em dois cilindros com uma ou mais cavidades centrais compostos por áreas integradas de abertura de cavidade, as áreas de ligação clinching, que propiciam a realização dos processos de união clinching contínuo e, ao mesmo tempo, a abertura de uma cavidade central tubular entre as duas chapas. o processo envolve, também, a redução de atrito entre as chapas por meio de lubrificação, proporcionando, através dos giros dos cilindros e dos esforços de compressão, a correta formação da cavidade central tubular. a tecnologia proposta pode ser utilizada em indústrias de transformação para confecção de peças tubulares para condução de fluidos, aplicáveis a sistemas de transferência de calor e transporte, tais como trocadores de calor. essa tecnologia representa uma forma mais simples, rápida e eficiente de produção de peças tubulares diante das tecnologias disponíveis atualmente em meios industriais.

column12: ELECTRONIC DEVICE AND METHOD FOR MONITORING AND CONTROLLING VEGETABLES GROWTH.
column13: The present disclosure is related to an electronic device for monitoring and controlling the growth of vegetables, through a measuring and handling method of physical and chemical variables, which sends monitoring data and control instructions through radio frequency signals. The device of this invention is characterized in that it comprises at least one processing module referred to as "SoC", which is a non-volatile storage module referred to as "memory", a communications module, a monitored module, a scheduled maintenance module referred to as "RT", a module for activation/deactivation of actuators referred to as "control" and a plurality of synchronous/asynchronous information channels.

column12: DNA MOLECULE CODING FOR A GAMMA-TOCOPHEROL METHYLTRANSFERASE IN MAIZE AND APPLICATIONS THEREOF
column13: The invention relates to a DNA molecule comprising: (a) a DNA sequence which is identified by SEQ ID No. 1, or (b) a DNA sequence similar to the latter, which (i) is essentially homologous to same and/or which (ii) codes for a polypeptide which is essentially homologous to the protein encoded by the above-mentioned DNA molecule. When introduced into a tocopherol-producing plant, principally maize, using standard biotechnology techniques, the aforementioned DNA molecule enables an increase in the total vitamin E content of said plant as wells in the concentrations of alpha and <-tocopherol. The invention can also be used for other applications.

column12: MOLECULAS DE ADN QUE CODIFICA PARA UNA GAMMA -TOCOFEROL METILTRANSFERASA DE MAIZ Y SUS APLICACIONES.
column13: Molécula de ADN que codifica para una gamma-tocoferol metiltransferasa de maíz y sus aplicaciones. Dicha molécula comprende (a) uña secuencia de ADN identificada por SEQ ID No. 1, o (b) una secuencia de ADN análoga a la misma que (i) es sustancialmente homóloga a ella, y/o que (ii) que codifica para un polipéptido que es sustancialmente homólogo a la proteína codificada por dicha molécula de ADN. Dicha molécula introducida en una planta productora de tocoferoles, principalmente maíz, por técnicas habituales en biotecnología, permite aumentar el contenido de vitamina E total en dicha planta, así como el contenido en {al} y {ga}{sup,-} tocoferol, entre otras aplicaciones.

column12: COOLING SYSTEM THROUGH THE ACQUISITION OF SOLAR HEAT.
column13: The present disclosure is related to a solar heat acquisition system, where a temperature exchange process is facilitated and used for climate conditioning in closed environments. The present invention is related to a solar heat acquisition system and a method of heat exchange to control the climate in a closed environment; which is related to domotics and can be applied for climate conditioning in work and conviviality areas. The present invention is related to a solar heat acquisition system for climate conditioning in closed environments. Calorific energy is stored using salts (nitrites, sodium nitrates or potassium nitrates), extracting the heat by mixing the salts with water.

column12: DNA molecule codifying a chlamydomonas dioxygenase comprising a protein and polypeptide monitor enhancing resistance to certain herbicides
column13: The DNA molecule codifying a chlamydomonas dioxygenase comprises a SEQ ID No.1 DNA sequence or an analogous DNA sequence for respective protein and polypeptide codification. Also claimed is a process using the molecule. CLAIMED PROCESS - The process increases alpha and gamma tocopherols content and also the total vitamin E content of plants producing tocopherols and enhances resistance to certain triketones and isoxazoles as herbicides. EMBODIMENT - The molecule codes a chlamydomonas dioxygenase p-hydroxyphenylpyruvate.

column12: Evaporative photovoltaic chimney for the simultaneous activation and dissipation of heat of an air conditioning system (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: Evaporative photovoltaic chimney for the simultaneous activation and heat dissipation of an air conditioning system. Evaporative photovoltaic chimney to cool the photovoltaic panel by means of an air current in its back part and dissipate the heat of a refrigeration cycle. The fireplace is divided into two main parts. The first section called evaporative zone has a series of nozzles that atomize water in parallel flow with the ambient air that descends. As the water falls a small part evaporates, cooling the rest. This section works as a small-scale cooling tower. The air that has been in contact with the water rises as a result of the flotation in the so-called convective zone. This second zone is basically a solar chimney in which the heating of the air causes the flotation of the same. At the same time, the air that rises through the convective section cools the photovoltaic panel, increasing its performance. (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)

column12: MOLECULA DE ADN QUE CODIFICA UNA P-HIDROXIFENILPIRUVATO DIOXIGENASA DE CHLAMYDOMONAS Y SUS APLICACIONES
column13: Molécula de ADN que codifica una p-hidroxifenilpiruvato dioxigenasa de chlamydomonas y sus aplicaciones. Dicha molécula comprende (a) una secuencia de ADN identificada por SEQ ID No.1, o (b) una secuencia de ADN análoga a la misma que (i) es sustancialmente homóloga a ella, y/o que (ii) codifica para un polipéptido que es sustancialmente homólogo a la proteína codificada por dicha secuencia de ADN definida en (a). Dicha molécula introducida en una planta productora de tocoferoles por técnicas habituales en biotecnología, permite aumentar el contenido de vitamina E total en dicha planta, así como el contenido en {al} y {ga}-tocoferol, entre otras aplicaciones, como aumentar la resistencia a ciertos herbicidas seleccionados del grupo formado por las tricetonas y los isoxazoles.

column12: PHOTOVOLTAIC EVAPORATIVE CHIMNEY FOR SIMULTANEOUS ACTUATION AND HEAT DISSIPATION IN AN AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEM
column13: The invention relates to a photovoltaic evaporative chimney for cooling a photovoltaic panel, using a current of air on the rear thereof, and for dissipating heat from a cooling cycle. The chimney is divided into two main parts. The first section, known as the evaporative zone, comprises a series of nozzles that spray water that flows parallel to the falling ambient air. As the water is falling a small part is evaporated, the remainder being cooled. This section operates as a small-scale cooling tower. The air that was in contact with the water floats up into the so-called convective zone. This second zone is basically a solar chimney in which the air is heated, causing said air to float. In turn the air rising through the convective section cools the photovoltaic panel, increasing the efficiency thereof. Fig. 1

column13: The present invention relates to a composition based on basidiomes of the edible fungus Pleurotus djamor for the control of the parasitic nematode of sheep Haemonchus Contortus characterized by a bioactive fraction and the production process thereof. column12: GAS-LIQUID-SOLID PRECIPITATION REACTOR
column13: The invention relates to a gas-liquid-solid precipitation reactor including scrubbing means (17, 18, 19, 20) associated with the lower outlet of a central tube (4) of an agitator (3), having an upper inlet through which a gas enters, said gas flowing through the central tube (4) and being released inside the lower part of the container (1) through a diffuser outlet (5), such as to bubble into a liquid reagent contained in the reactor. The aforementioned scrubbing means (17, 18, 19, 20) enable the simultaneous precipitation and discharge of solid particles contained in the gas when bubbled, without the reactor having to be stopped. The draining of the solids is facilitated with the use of a trap disk (24) on the internal base of the container (1), the upper face of which is provided with descending grooves (25) which direct the solids towards the base of the container (1) by means of agitation.

column12: REACTOR DE PRECIPITACION GAS-LIQUIDO-SOLIDO.
column13: Reactor de precipitación gas-líquido-sólido. Incorpora medios de limpieza (17, 18, 19, 20) asociados a la boca de salida inferior de un tubo central (4) de un agitador (3) por cuya entrada superior penetra un gas que atraviesa el tubo central (4) y desemboca inferiormente en el interior del depósito (1) a través de un difusor de salida (5) borboteando en un líquido reaccionante contenido en el reactor. Estos medios de limpieza (17, 18, 19, 20) permiten, de forma simultánea y sin necesidad de detener el reactor, la precipitación y salida de las partículas sólidas contenidas en el gas al tiempo que es borboteado. Asimismo se facilita el escurrido de los sólidos mediante un disco trampa (24) situado en el interior y sobre la base del depósito (1) que está dotado de unas acanaladuras descendentes (25) en su cara superior que dirige los sólidos hacia el fondo del depósito (1) por un movimiento de agitación.

column12: FOOD ADDITIVE WITH HIGH FIBER CONTENT FOR WHOLE DIETS OF SMALL RUMINANTS.
column13: The present invention relates to the field of food products, particularly fodder as animal feed. It aims to increase the nutritional value of vegetable fibers used as a food additive. Also, it uses agro-industrial by-products as additive ingredients for animal feed for ruminant nutrition, enabling good consumption, digestibility, and weight gain. Additionally, it provides a food additive with a high fiber content for integral diets of small ruminants, containing an exhausted substrate from a Pleurotus spp fungus culture, including a mixture in equal parts of cob, grass, and coffee pulp.

column12: SHOCK ABSORBER FOR VEHICLES
column13: The present invention relates to a shock absorber (1) for vehicles comprising a cylinder (2) with a longitudinal shaft (LS) filled with a non-Newtonian shear thickening fluid (STF) along which a plunger (3) moves longitudinally. The cross-section of the plunger (3) is smaller than an inner cross-section of the cylinder (2) to allow the STF to pass through a space between said plunger (3) and an inner wall of the cylinder (2). Furthermore, the plunger (3) is configured such that the resistance offered by the STF against the movement of the plunger (3) along a first direction of movement is different from the resistance offered by the STF against the movement of the plunger (3) along a second direction of movement opposite to the first.

column12: NON-DESTRUCTIVE PROCESS FOR ELIMINATING SILICON FROM ALUMINA-BASED MATERIALS
column13: The present invention relates to a process for eliminating silicon and/or silicon compounds contained in alumina-based materials without destruction thereof, permitting reutilisation thereof, and consequently application principally lies in regeneration of silicon-contaminated alumina-based catalysts used in hydrotreatment processes in the petroleum industry to eliminate sulphur and remove silicon from process streams. In this respect it is important to note that known conventional procedures and/or methods for eliminating or removing silicon contained in alumina-based materials utilise an inorganic acid or mixtures thereof by digestion, the same modifying the properties of the alumina and of any other element contained in the material, destroying the alumina and preventing reutilisation thereof. The non-destructive process of the present invention is characterised in that it employs an extraction agent which depolymerises silicon compounds deposited on alumina-based materials without modifying the properties of the alumina-based material and without substantially modifying the content of other substances or metals present in the alumina-based material. The extraction agent is an alcohol, preferably a polyol, more preferably glycerol, a commercially-available material not requiring a high degree of purity for the application thereof. The silicon contained in the alumina-based material to which the non-destructive process of the present invention is applied is preferably in inorganic form, oxide and silanol: Si-(OX) 4 (X = Al, H, Si) and/or in organic form, organosilanes: (OX) 3 -Si-CH 3 and/or (CH 3 ) 2 -Si-(OX) 2 (X = H, Si); both structures are depolymerised through employing this removal process.

column12: COMPOSITION BASED ON A DEGRADED SUBSTRATE OF P. OSTREATUS FOR CONTROLLING HAEMONCHUS CONTORTUS AND THE OBTAINING PROCESS THEREOF.
column13: The present invention relates to a nematicidal extract obtained from the exhausted or degraded substrate of the edible fungus Pleurotus ostreatus, as well as its production process. Said extract allows controlling the hatching of eggs of the parasite Haemonchus Contortus and its larval stage. Also, the present invention relates to a pharmaceutical composition comprising the nematicidal extract and one or more pharmaceutically acceptable excipients. Further, it can be subjected to a silica gel column fractionation with the solvent system hexane and the ethyl acetate for showing that the fractions obtained with the solvent in the ratio 3:1 to 4:1 preserve the nematicidal activity.

column12: Non-destructive process for the elimination of silicon from alumina based materials
column13: A method for eliminating silicon or silicon compounds in alumina based materials without destroying such alumina based materials enabling reutilization particularly in catalysts for hydrotreating processes, comprising: a) mixing alumina based solid material which contains silicon with an alcohol extraction agent at a temperature between 10 and 300° C., for 10 minutes to 96 hours to form a mixture; b) separating solids from the mixture by centrifugation, decantation or filtration to obtain separated solids; c) washing the separated solids with at least one of water, alcohol or an ammonium hydroxide solution to form washed solids; and d) drying the washed solids to obtain regenerated alumina based solid material.

column12: Non-destructive process for the elimination of silicon from alumina based materials
column13: The present invention refers to a method for eliminating silicon or silicon compounds that are contained in alumina based materials without destroying such alumina based materials allowing for their reutilization, its main application is being the regeneration of alumina based catalyst contaminated with silicon, which are used in hydro-treating processes in the oil industry for sulfur elimination and silicon removal from process streams. It is important to note that the procedures and/or conventional methods known so far for the elimination and removal of silicon contained in alumina based materials, use inorganic acids or their mixture in a digestion process which modifies the properties of alumina and of any other element contained in the material, thus destroying the alumina and disabling their reutilization. The non-destructive method of the present invention is characterized by the fact that an extraction agent depolymerize the silicon compounds deposited in alumina based materials, with no modification of the properties of the alumina based material and with no substantial modification of other materials o or on the metal content present in the alumina based material. The extraction agent used is an alcohol, preferably a polyol and more preferably glycerol, which is available needless of high grade of purity for its use. The silicon contained in alumina based materials, in which the non-destructive method of the present invention is used, is preferably found in inorganic structures such as oxide or silanol: Si—(OX) 4 (X═Al, H, Si) and/or as organosilanes structures: (OX) 3 —Si—CH 3 and/or (CH 3 ) 2 —Si—(OX) 2 (X═H, Si), both are depolymerized when this removal method is used.

column13: Un dispositivo disipador sismico para pavimentos desplazables caracterizado porque comprende una entrejunta de forma paralelepipeda (1), cuatro resortes de elastomero (2) que estan embebidos parcialmente en la entrejunta de forma paralelepipeda (1) y en cuyos extremos se ubican unas argollas sujetadoras (3), donde los resortes de elastomero (2) diametralmente opuestos son colineales. Un dispositivo disipador sismico, segun la reivindicacion 1 caracterizado porque dos resortes de elastomero (2) colineales, son respecto a los otros dos, no coplanares entre si. Un dispositivo disipador sismico, segun la reivindicacion 1 caracterizado porque la entrejunta de forma paralelepipeda (2) es de forma cubica.

column12: TRANSGENIC RABBITS WHICH EXPRESS HUMAN GROWTH HORMONE IN THE MILK OF THE FEMALE
column13: LA PRESENTE INVENCION SE RELACIONA CON EL CAMPO DE LA INGENIERIA GENETICA Y LA BIOTECNOLOGIA, Y ESPECIFICAMENTE CON LA OBTENCION DE ANIMALES TRANSGENICOS. ESTA INVENCION PERSIGUE EL OBJETIVO DE OBTENER UNA RAZA DE CONEJOS CAPACES DE PRODUCIR UNA PROTEINA FORANEA, EN PARTICULAR LA HORMONA DEL CRECIMIENTO HUMANO, EN LA LECHE DE SUS HEMBRAS. PARA ELLO EL GENOMA DE UNA RAZA DE CONEJOS HA SIDO MODIFICADO MEDIANTE LA INTRODUCCION DE UN SEGMENTO DE ACIDO DESOXIRIBONUCLEICO (ADN) QUE CONTIENE LA INFORMACION NECESARIA PARA LA SINTESIS Y SECRECION EN LA LECHE DE LA PROTEINA HUMANA. MEDIANTE CRUZAMIENTOS SE OBTUVIERON LOS ANIMALES DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA GENERACION PARA EL NUEVO CARACTER, CON LOS CUALES SE OBTUVO UNA LINEA ESTABLE DE CONEJOS TRANSGENICOS. ESTA LINEA DE ANIMALES TRANSGENICOS ES DE GRAN UTILIDAD PARA ESTUDIOS ENCAMINADOS A DESCIFRAR LOS MECANISMOS DE SECRECION DE PROTEINAS A LA LECHE DE LOS MAMIFEROS, ASI COMO PARA LA OBTENCION DE DETERMINADAS CANTIDADES DE ESTA PROTEINA HUMANA CORRECTAMENTE CONFORMADA Y ACTIVA PARA ENSAYOS ANALITICOS, E IGUALMENTE PARA ESTUDIOS SOBRE EL FUNCIONAMIENTO DE LOS DIFERENTES ELEMENTOS DE CONTROL QUE INTEGRAN EL TRANSGEN EN DIFERENTES TEJIDOS Y DURANTE LAS DIFERENTES ETAPAS DE LA VIDA DEL ANIMAL.\!

column12: SHEET CONTAINING A THERMOPLASTIC ELASTOMER, PREPARATION METHOD AND USE
column13: A sheet comprising a support layer made of a textile, a cover layer on the support layer, and a compound structure, wherein the cover layer contains a thermoplastic elastomer, and wherein the compound structure consists of a part of the support layer and a part of the cover layer interpenetrating each other, wherein the extent of interpenetration, defined as [(thickness of the compound structure)/(thickness of the cover layer)] x 100 %, is 5 % to 99 %; a method of preparing the sheet; and the use of the sheet as a surface material in the interior of a vehicle.

column12: MONITORING AND ALERTING SYSTEM FOR THE PRESERVATION OF HEALTH.
column13: The present invention relates to a system and its process, through a technological platform for monitoring and alerting, which prevents infections or abnormalities early for the preservation of the health of confined people. It is useful in centers, educational institutions, lodgings, restaurants, and/or in any type of events, where there is an intention, obligation or need to take care of the health of individuals and people, generating timely information so that the entity and/or the medical service or health institutions take actions in each case presented by the platform. The Platform receives information from various peripheral devices (personal or mass capture) that emit signals, considered as sensors used to measure vital signs.

column12: AERO-TORSO.
column13: The present disclosure is related to an aero-torso with multi-rotor air vehicle type characteristics, which is composed of at least two aero-arms rigidly attached to a main multi-rotor working as a waist. The main multi-rotor has a flexible mechanical coupling to compensate the undesired movements. Each aero-arm is formed of at least one (shoulder) or two (shoulder and elbow) multi-rotors; said multi-rotor allows movements in 3 dimensions, translational and rotational. The systems described herein provide an aero-torso capable of being transformed from a first to a second configuration in order to increase the functional space for matter manipulation.

column12: material flexível, método de obtenção e seus usos.
column13: material flexível, método de obtenção e seus usos. a presente divulgação refere-se a um material flexível que imita o couro, mais em particular, um material têxtil revestido com produtos de origem vegetal. a presente divulgação refere-se a um material flexível compreendido por um substrato têxtil, tecido, malha, ou não tecido, revestido, cujo material de revestimento possui na sua constituição, resíduos e subprodutos vegetais que podem ser de diferentes tipologias. em particular, os têxteis possuem resíduos ligados ao substrato têxtil por utilização de um ligante. o material flexível da presente divulgação é útil para a indústria têxtil e de confecção, podendo ser aplicado extensivamente na indústria têxtil, nomeadamente na fabricação de materiais têxteis para vestuário ou para aplicação em mobiliário, têxteis-lar e decoração, calçado, estofados de automóvel, malas, carteiras, cintos, marroquinaria, etc.

column12: FLEXIBLE MATERIAL, ITS PRODUCTION METHOD AND USES
column13: The present disclosure relates to a flexible material which imitates leather, more in particular a textile material, coated with products of vegetable origin. The present disclosure relates to a flexible material comprised of a coated textile substrate, woven, knitted or non-woven fabric, the coating material of which having in its constitution vegetable by-products and residues, which may be of different typologies. In particular, the textiles have residues attached to the textile substrate through the use of a binder. The flexible material of the present disclosure is useful for the textile and confectionery industry and can be extensively applied in the textile industry namely in the manufacture of textile materials for clothing or for application in furniture, home textiles and decoration, footwear, automobile upholstery, bags, wallets, belts, leather goods, etc.

column12: FLEXIBLE MATERIAL, METHOD OF OBTAINING AND USES THEREOF
column13: The present disclosure relates to a flexible imitation-leather material, in particular a textile material coated with products of plant origin. The present disclosure relates to a flexible material formed by a textile substrate, a coated woven, knitted or nonwoven fabric, the coating material containing plant waste and bye-products of different types. In particular, the textiles comprise waste bonded to the textile substrate by a binder. The flexible material according to the present disclosure is useful in the textile and garment industry and can be extensively used in the textile industry, namely for producing textile materials for garments or for use in furniture, home and home decoration textiles, footwear, car upholstery, suitcases, wallets, belts, leather goods, etc.
